WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.100 --> 00:00:06.650
STEPHEN CARPENTER: I have two
activities that I've prepared.

00:00:06.650 --> 00:00:10.280
So interpretation, this idea
of constructing meanings

00:00:10.280 --> 00:00:15.080
or developing meanings
about works of art,

00:00:15.080 --> 00:00:16.550
or we can think
of interpretation

00:00:16.550 --> 00:00:19.760
as someone is
speaking one language

00:00:19.760 --> 00:00:22.880
and then we take that
language and we are able to--

00:00:22.880 --> 00:00:25.230
not only do we speak and
understand this language,

00:00:25.230 --> 00:00:31.260
then we can take those
ideas and those words

00:00:31.260 --> 00:00:33.510
and turn them into
a different language

00:00:33.510 --> 00:00:35.290
that someone else speaks.

00:00:35.290 --> 00:00:38.020
We can have interpretation
function in that way as well.

00:00:38.020 --> 00:00:40.650
So it's about taking
ideas from one context

00:00:40.650 --> 00:00:44.580
into another or one mode of
representation in communication

00:00:44.580 --> 00:00:45.550
into another.

00:00:45.550 --> 00:00:48.690
But in terms of art
and art practice,

00:00:48.690 --> 00:00:54.740
art criticism and
interpretation work together.

00:00:54.740 --> 00:01:03.070
So this image I think is
useful for our purposes here.

00:01:03.070 --> 00:01:10.630
Imagine that this
image was the poster

00:01:10.630 --> 00:01:17.530
for a movie, full length,
feature length movie.

00:01:17.530 --> 00:01:21.790
And imagine you were responsible
for writing the copy--

00:01:21.790 --> 00:01:28.890
for writing the text for the
voiceover of the movie trailer,

00:01:28.890 --> 00:01:32.820
but all you had was
this image to go by.

00:01:32.820 --> 00:01:35.400
You probably heard
movie trailers,

00:01:35.400 --> 00:01:38.220
those little
commercials for movies.

00:01:38.220 --> 00:01:41.130
And usually my
experience, they start off

00:01:41.130 --> 00:01:44.670
with one of two phrases or a
version of one of two phrases.

00:01:44.670 --> 00:01:47.340
One of the phrases
is usually something

00:01:47.340 --> 00:01:53.260
like this, "Imagine a
place--" And you can imagine--

00:01:53.260 --> 00:01:55.584
you've heard this phrase
before from movie trailers.

00:01:55.584 --> 00:01:58.000
"Imagine a place" and the
music is start doing [HUMMING]..

00:01:58.000 --> 00:01:59.480
You see the scenery.

00:01:59.480 --> 00:02:05.636
Another phrase that is often
used is "In a world where--"

00:02:05.636 --> 00:02:06.135
You've--

00:02:06.135 --> 00:02:08.938
I see nodding going on,
so that means, oh, I've--

00:02:08.938 --> 00:02:10.479
you could probably
name several films

00:02:10.479 --> 00:02:12.680
that have movie trailers
that start that way.

00:02:12.680 --> 00:02:14.350
So take one of those phrases--

00:02:14.350 --> 00:02:20.111
"imagine a place," or
"in a world--" and--

00:02:20.111 --> 00:02:22.110
I don't know if you have
something to write with

00:02:22.110 --> 00:02:24.580
or if you want to
keep it in your head.

00:02:24.580 --> 00:02:28.020
And if you come up a sentence
or two, that would be great.

00:02:28.020 --> 00:02:31.320
But the sentence or two that
starts with one of those two

00:02:31.320 --> 00:02:36.510
prompts would function as
the beginning voiceover copy

00:02:36.510 --> 00:02:39.570
for the movie from
which this still comes.

00:02:39.570 --> 00:02:40.170
We got it?

00:02:40.170 --> 00:02:40.680
All right.

00:02:40.680 --> 00:02:41.721
Here's the movie trailer.

00:02:41.721 --> 00:02:43.380
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:02:43.380 --> 00:02:46.890
- What would you do in
a world without justice?

00:02:46.890 --> 00:02:50.820
In 2017, humankind's
most precious resource

00:02:50.820 --> 00:02:54.000
is used as a weapon of control.

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:57.631
Will you punch up against power?

00:02:57.631 --> 00:02:59.404
[END PLAYBACK]

00:02:59.404 --> 00:03:01.195
STEPHEN CARPENTER: I'm
going to that movie.

00:03:01.195 --> 00:03:03.682
[LAUGHS] Wow, all right.

00:03:03.682 --> 00:03:04.890
So part of what I'm hearing--

00:03:04.890 --> 00:03:10.590
